{
  "texts": [
    "Typically, it is distinguished whether a problem is in complexity class P or NP (see e.g.",
    "Whitley 2013; Homer and Selman 2011).",
    "In practice, the complexity class P (polynomial) can be thought of as all problems that are deemed tractable, which means that they can be solved in reasonable-i.e.",
    "polynomial-computation time (Homer and Selman 2011).",
    "The complexity class NP (non-deterministic polynomial) is the set of problems that are solvable in polynomial time on a non-deterministic Turing."
  ]
}